Not implemented yet. Current jj support already adds `targets-change` edges to commit notes and `read`/`follow` can fall back by change_id after rewrites. What is still missing is a bulk `migrate` command that scans commit notes, resolves the current commit for each change_id, and reattaches or copies notes when rewritten commit OIDs diverge.

An MVP should probably do: --dry-run, apply on the current notes ref, and skip conflicts.
